column1: # curie_map: # This contains the URLs prefixes used in the mapping file
#   skos: http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core# ### Always needed. Do not modify
#   sssom: https://w3id.org/sssom/             ### Always needed. Do not modify
#   subject:  https://pypi.org/ns/core-metadata# ### Value of the schema. Need to be changed.
#   codemeta: "https://w3id.org/codemeta/3.0/" ### Always needed. Do not modify
#   schema: "http://schema.org/" ### Always needed. Do not modify

# mapping_set_description: 'Mapping between codemeta and core metadata specification of the PyPa Package Distribution Metadata (https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/specifications/core-metadata/). We have followed the structure of the JSON provided by the API(e.g. https://pypi.org/pypi/somef/json)' ### Please
column2: add the description of your mapping
add a URI of the author of the mapping. Prioritize ORCIDs for persons and ROR ids for organizations
add a URI of your crosswalk. You can use the w3id.org service to create it.

column9: Deprecated property. Use classifiers['License']. Example: License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License.
If the license in Codemeta is a URL.
If the license in Codemeta is a CreativeWork. The codemeta term has a path license/name.
Since version 2.4. It only applies to CreativeWork. Example: MIT AND (Apache-2.0 OR BSD-2-Clause). The codemeta term has a path license/name.
It may include the email in the string.The codemeta term has a path author/name.
It may include the name in the string.The codemeta term has a path author/email.
It may include the email in the string.The codemeta term has a path maintainer/name.
It may include the name in the string.The codemeta term has a path maintainer/email.
Example: Programming Language :: Python :: 3. It appears more python version as list.Use classifiers['programming Language'].
